        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=# Instructions for Writing a Cover Letter and Question Responses\n\nYou will be provided with a job listing from UpWork containing:\n\n1. **UpWork URL** (required)\n2. **Job Title** (required)\n3. **Job Description** (required)\n4. **Question 1** (optional)\n5. **Question 2** (optional)\n6. **Question 3** (optional)\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Write a Cover Letter (7 Paragraphs)\n- Read and analyze the provided job listing.\n- Write a **7-paragraph cover letter** in a simple, 7th-grade reading level.\n  \n#### Structure:\n1. **Introduction:** Hook the reader with your enthusiasm for the role and why you‚Äôre great at what you do. Mention key skills. Avoid: \"I am very excited to apply...\"\n2. **Body Paragraphs (1-5):** Discuss your qualifications, experience, and why you‚Äôre a good fit for this specific role and company. Highlight relevant skills and recent work based on the job description.\n3. **Conclusion:** Summarize why you‚Äôre perfect for the role. Show eagerness to interview.\n\n#### Notes for the Cover Letter:\n- Use **short sentences** and **simple words**.\n- Avoid passive voice, filler words, or unnecessary details.\n- Keep a **friendly, professional tone**.\n- No personal details‚Äîstart directly with the cover letter.\n- End with a clear call to action, like scheduling an interview.\n- Ensure the letter is easy to read (Hemingway level) and suitable for a single page.\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Write Responses to Job Questions\n- If any **optional questions** are provided, write clear and detailed responses for each.\n- Use the same **7th-grade reading level** and **direct approach**.\n\n---\n\n### Response Format:\nReturn each part of the response in a **JSON object** as follows:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"Cover Letter\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"Answer 1\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"Answer 2\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"Answer 3\": \"string (optional)\"\n}",
              "role": "system"
            },
            {
              "content": "=Job Title: {{ $json['Job Listing Title'] }}\nJob Description: {{ $json.Description }}\nQuestion 1: {{ $json.fields['Additional Question #1'] }}\nQuestion 2: {{ $json.fields['Additional Question #2'] }}\nQuestion 3: {{ $json.fields['Additional Question #3'] }}"
            }
          ]
        },
